    "Figure 4 illustrates the distribution of these reward samples, along with their mean value.",
    "The mean value serves as an accurate and unbiased estimation of the state-value function 𝑉 𝜋 (𝑠).",
    "It is worth noting that prior studies [4,57], have utilized a single trajectory's cumulative discounted reward to estimate either the state-value function 𝑉 𝜋 (𝑠) or the state-action value function 𝑄 𝜋 (𝑠, 𝑎), which suffers from the issue of high variance estimation.",
